column5: Got off early from work, so I decided to take a walk out onto Cooks by Lefroy. Setting up the portable was like flying a kite, drilled a hole there was a good 14 inches of ice.  Dropped a minnow down and within seconds got one. For 2 hours it was the same thing, the only reason I didnt have a bite in 10 seconds was if the previous fish took the minnow.  Took home 12 bigger then the average this year for some dinner and freezer. Might get out again on Saturday.
Nice, my Dad lives up there in belly wart. Was up on Friday saw about 8 others in the ice. Always nice to have the option to just walk out an fish.
What's with the wind everyday lol ?.You had a good day!,the perch sizes the last week or so are unbelieveable!!Hope to get a few more on Sunday as well.
